< review>
Awesome place for clothing, shoes, accessories and more.
It's a great place for your pre- teen, teen or for any young adult who wants to be trendy and get things in great condition and you won't have to spend a lot of money. Great prices.
Great selection of girls and guys fashions and accessories like jewelry, purses, hats, bathing suits and boots and shoes. They also have a large selection of sweaters, jackets and coats.
Everything has a many size selections.  The staff were extremely helpful and friendly.
We are going back again soon.
We loved it. I highly recommend Plato's Closet.< /review>

< review>
Although Plato's certainly has a good amount of trendy and current outfit options, I feel that they could expand on the male section a bit. The store itself isn't very large, which results in about 2 short aisles dedicated to what people might generally recognize as male outfits.
That said, they have a good selection of women's shoes and sunglasses, kind and helpful staff, and a decent property location. Have fun!</review>

<Text>Neat little place to sell your clothes. Of course your not going to get rich selling, but hey it's a business, and you get a few bucks in return for stuff you were probably going to donate anyways. They mostly have women's clothing, but there's a decent smaller section for guys. Good place to find some the stuff you'd see at the Del Monte Center, but for less! Note there's a cutoff time for them to purchase clothing, about an hour or so before they close. Just call to verify it ahead of time. Check it out!<//Text>< gmap_id>

<Rate>5<//Rate><Resp>{'time': 1581627108669, 'text': "Hi Allison,  Thank you for sharing your review! We're so happy to hear you had such a wonderful time and will certainly pass on your kind words to Theo, we hope you can visit us again soon!\n\nCheers,\nThe Chappellet Team"}<//Resp>< review>
We had the most exquisite and special experience visiting Chappellet this weekend. Thank you so much to the incredible staff for making our visit so lovely. And an even bigger thank you to Theo, who led our wine tasting tour! Theo is the BEST! She has such a passion for wine and how wine is made. We learned so much from Theo and appreciated the little touches she went out of her way to make our experience so unique. The wines we tasted were on a spectrum from delicious to exquisite! Every wine was well balanced and full of flavor. There aren't that many family owned wineries left in Napa, and it was a pleasure to learn so much about the Chappellet family and the decades of passion and hard work they've put in to make sure their wine is not only exquisite but also a reflection of their family's character and integrity. So thank you, Chappellet, and especially Theo for making our visit so lovely!< /review>

<Text>Everything about Chappellet is amazing... the views and the wine are phenomenal. <userid>117461522538299956650</userid>< username>
Kurt Rose< /username>
<time>1536424207361</time><Rating>5</Rating>< Review>
A beautiful place with great wines.

Our friends are members and they had set up a tasting experience.  We were taken to a "room" in the barrel house with "walls" of stacked barrels.  We sat at a nice table while the server stood and walked us through the various wines.

After our tasting we went to the "meadow" and had a picnic with a bottle we purchased and some food we had picked up at a Trader Joe's.  The meadow was very attractive with a beautiful view of vineyards, mountains and the big lake.  It was a very enjoyable and relaxing experience.</Review>

<Text>A little known, hidden gem in the middle of nowhere, this 2 hour tour is very much worth with the visit. Our tour guide, Will, is personable and humorous. The pathway to the cavern was just recently built or renovated within a year or so. This place was privately owned and hand-built by a couple who later passed away in the 1980‚Äôs then sold off to the State Parks. Lots of cool facts about this place that I‚Äôd consider still part of recent history.

Pricing: $10 adult, $5 children and $10 parking.

Fun facts I learned: this limestone cavern is so solid it withstand earthquakes. A great hideout place in natural disaster.

This place deserves more attention and protection. Really worth the drive to pay a visit. A nice walk through living history.< /Text><pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPD_zNt0Q5vFik7plapDKlH6WdhyOQQE8BOb2mT=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': < Review>
This is the most amazing place in the world. Do not go, unless you call well ahead and obtain confirmed cavern-tour reservations.  Forty people per day, weekends only. Seriously, search for the telephone number and call two to three months ahead for reservations. If you heed my directive... and call ahead... Maybe. Otherwise, forget it. You are wasting your time. No last-minute cancellations... believe me.

Look for the skinny Cave Wolf in my pictures. If you believe, you will see her. She is there.< /Review>

< text>
What an amazing place! The history you learn about the Mitchell Caverns is incredibly interesting. Learning how the Caverns formed to how one family tried to capitalize on them and they ultimately ended up as a state recreation area inside a National Preserve is a fun journey through time. Be sure to allow time to explore the little museum and adjoining trails. You'll see some of the best views the Mojave Desert has to offer.< /text>

<rating>4<//rating>< Text>
It's a learning curve. The tour guide is full of information and history back from the begining. The two caverns are smaller than i though. The ranger qont take the big group because it's hard to control. We cannot touch anything in the cavern. With the big group you wont be able to see or hear anything in front. It's quite a distance to get there unless you came from Barstow or Needle.< /Text>

<Pictures>None</Pictures>< review>
This park has been recently renovated in last 2018 or so, so the play structure is brand new along with the drinking fountains which pour out cold, clean water (a bonus here in the heat of Elk Grove). They also have 2 tennis courts, 1 basketball hoop, and a baseball field as well. The grassy area at this park is vast, so you can easily play any kind of game with your family. A few benches are dotted around the park with ample sade from the surrounding trees. Lastly, this park is generally not busy, so you can enjoy your time here in peace.</review>

< review>
Last cleaning
To preface this I'd have to say that I hadn't been to the dentist for a year before this recent cleaning, which is around the time of this review. My teeth were thoroughly cleaned. I found out I grind my teeth at night at this cleaning. This is the first time I've heard this news and luckily they caught it early enough to were there's still a chance to protect my teeth. Some other problems were caught quickly. X-Rays were pretty quick and painless. Found out I had to have some fillings fixed, and Dr. Chen was able to do it on the spot within a reasonable time. He administered anesthesia in a very quick and painless way. An added plus is that Dr. Chen is very friendly and easy to talk to.

Previous Cleanings
Very quick and clean. I had a different dentist at this time and he was really good too. Guess this place has always been good to me. This particular dentist, who is retired at this time, also managed to pull out both my lower wisdom teeth  within 5 minutes.

Overall:
I've never had second thoughts about going here.</review>

< review>
The experiance at Parkside Dental begins with Dr. Williams staff of customer service
oriented people who are very, very well trained and at all times professional.

My needs were evaluated and a treatment plan was thoroughly presented to me
with options, priorities and a very affordable finance plan.  The procedures I needed
were extensive (multiple root canals, tooth extractions and a very, very long bridge)
so the appointments were scheduled in order to maximize the amount of work done at each visit without spending a lot of time in the chair.  Also, Megan, who assisted Dr. Williams and was there each time I came in, was amazing.  She knew my history
and consistantly explained what I could expect at each visit.

Appointments were ALLWAYS ON TIME and I was not left sitting in the chair
for an extended period of time while I was being rotated with other patients.

Having required an extensive amount of dental work done prior to seeing Dr. Williams I can tell you from experience that Parkside Dental is the best.</review>

<username>Samantha Emerick<//username><time>1546984146048</time>< Text>
I needed to make a newer edit for my review, because I've been back to Parkside since I posted the original.
In November, I noticed that one of my clear retainers was broken, so I called Parkside to see if they could fit me in while I would be in town visiting some friends. Honestly, I thought it was a long shot, and that they couldn't. Imagine my surprise when I was booked a Saturday morning appointment with the ortho clinic.
Once in the chair, I explained the issue, and they went right to work. Dr. K examined my bite and when she was finished, Myron took an impression and said they could have my new retainer to me before I left the next week.
The best part, though? EVERYONE remembered me! I thought it was cool to see 98% of the same people at the clinic, but that all of them knew me by sight and were excited to see me? Wow, you guys. Customer service will NEVER EVER get better than that. They asked about both my kids (who had been patients there), and my husband (who usually came in with us), too! I felt so . . . loved? Appreciated? Cared for? I don't know, all of the above.
If you're looking for a dentists office where you can get all of your needs met, and have the staff feel like family, Parkside Dental is FAR AND AWAY the best choice! You absolutely can't go wrong as a patient here!

I've been a patient at Parkside Dental Care with Dr. Williams for several years.  Right off the bat, he came highly recommended for an excellent "chair-side" manner and quality healthcare.  The support staff in the office got rave reviews for their friendliness, the ease of making/rescheduling appointments, and how helpful they were with any questions.
To say that I was skeptical of such glowing terms would be an understatement.  I'm not a fan of the dentist, so I withheld all judgements until afterwards.  Imagine my surprise when all of those compliments were proven to be facts.
Early on, Dr. Williams recommended that I get braces.  He told me the usual things, how worth it the hassle would be in the end, how great it would be to have a beautiful smile after so long hiding my teeth.  It took me a while, but I came around.  First, to Dr. Ahn for oral surgery (also a great experience, outside of the expected pain and bruising of half my face that made staying inside for a week a necessity), and then across the hall to Dr. K for Orthodontics.
Seriously, there isn't enough nice things to say about Dr. K's staff (as well as Dr. K herself) and the quality of care that I have received in her office.  Francisco is always SO patient when working with my crazy schedule - and believe me, it takes an effort to make appointments work, at times.  Christina stays on top of the billing for my care, and if there are any problems, I know immediately. She's taken the time to answer numerous questions and run out all payment options so that I can be sure I'm getting a service at a price that I'm comfortable with.  It makes going through this hassle a little bit easier, knowing my account is in capable hands.
The technicians, Darlene, Shannon, Myron, and Danielle, always treat my family and I like they're stoked to see us that day, which I find that I look forward to with each visit.  There's something to having a friendly relationship with the people that are going to have their hands in your mouth for the duration of your treatment.

I recommend this office to everyone I know who's in the market for a dentist.  As I said in the beginning of my review, I'm not a huge fan of the dentist, but I'm glad to say that I go to Parkside.  They've done a wonderful job of changing my opinion and I can't wait to see the end results of my orthodontic treatment.< /Text>

< Review>
I updated this review after being helped by Romeo and the Katherine for different issues with smoking and loud music from a neighbor.

This will be my third year at Ava burbank. Currently I'm renting a one bedroom on one of the north pass Ave apartments on a second floor. Most of the time its quiet and peaceful with the community and I haven't really had an issue with packages/mail other than when the post office misdelivers it to the building next door. In that case the resident messaged me and I was able to grab it quick. For most amazon packages they have an Amazon hub which is a secure way to pick up my stuff anytime. The only time they don't use that is for large/oversized packages. I used the hub excessively especially during the last year and even during the midst of covid had little to no issues.

The apartment itself is well maintained I've only needed to call maintenence 3 times in three years for the toilet and a buzzing ac but in each case they showed up the same day and it was fixed either shortly or the next day in the case of the ac because they gave me a new one.

The sound is blocked better in the bedroom/kitchen and bathroom. I can hear loud bass if my downstairs neighbor is playing it and you'll know if someone is smoking in their apartment from your kitchen at least in my case.

For the sound I had an issue with loud bass but Katherine the community manager has been great with reaching out to the other resident and trying to resolve the issue in a way that both apartments can continue to live and work peacefully.

For the smoking issue the building is smoke free and Romeo the leasing agent I worked with was able to take care of that after a few months beyond what actions I took to filter the air with filtration devices.

In these cases I had nothing against Ava and I tried different things to resolve it peacefully, just be sure to reach out if your having an issue so the staff can work with you.

Some positives are there are several grocery and restaurants only a few blocks away depending on your building. Gym and pools, A weekly food truck that comes by the leasing office. You pay rent online and they lowered rates recently at least for my unit which is saving me several hundred a month. The laundry uses an app that gives you time estimates and is in a shared spot in my building but I think some buildings or apartments have them in unit.

Hope this helps.< /Review>

<user_id>118253613905949364314</user_id><user_name>Ross Hayduk< /user_name>< Date>
1575063293141< /Date>
< Rate>
5< /Rate>
<Text>When I moved from Northern California to the Los Angeles area, I did not have a lot of options, because I am a dog owner.  But when I found AVA Burbank, I knew I was "home".

First and foremost, Brendan Sund in the leasing office was a lifesaver.  He helped me find the best unit available to fit my needs and let me know that AVA Burbank would accommodate my furry friend.  During the course of shopping for the unit and all along the path to moving in and getting settled, Brendan has gone above and beyond with amazing support and service.

Why do I love AVA Burbank?  Let me count the ways...

1) A modern refresh of classic architecture...  it feels "retro" without feeling "old".  I live in a 450 sq ft studio and I am happy as a clam.  Tons of built-in storage...  I almost got rid of some of my furniture because there is so much storage in the unit.

2) My unit has a reserved parking spot with a BIG storage locker that can accommodate six of those large Costco black & yellow storage bins.

3) A great little pool surrounded by palm trees and patio furniture, complete with a HUGE gas grill.

4) Pet-friendly buildings, with complimentary dog waste bags at the door and waste stations along the sidewalks to capture bags.  The tree-lined neighborhood is perfect for dogs...  flat, quiet, and full of SQUIRRELS!!  An off-leash dog park is available a few miles away in North Hollywood.

5) A large complex (with plenty of support services) made up of over a dozen smaller buildings, which makes for a cozier environment where you recognize your neighbors and the building does not turn into a party palace.

6) A Von's grocery store next door and equidistant Trader Joe's and Whole Foods in the neighborhood.  A variety of restaurants within walking distance for when you don't feel like cooking.  Also, a Starbucks across the street to help start the day.

7) The madness of LA is just across the hill and is a short drive to Hollywood...  but Burbank is so insulated from the City, it feels like it is hours away.

8) Just a short drive to Burbank's shopping centers, so IKEA, Target/WalMart, Home Depot/Lowe's, Macy's, REI, and many more are within a few miles of AVA Burbank, without requiring a drive to Glendale or Los Angeles.

9) A short walk to the Burbank Media District...  Warner Brother's Studio is just down the street, and it is a quick hop to Disney Studios and NBC Comcast Universal, as well as the media production schools.

AND...

10) Just around the corner from the famous Bob's Big Boy!</Text>< Pics>
None< /Pics>

<Text>I've been here 3.5 years now and haven't had any complaints. I remember reading negative reviews before I moved in here but none of them have been part of my experience. Tania has been here as long as I have, which shows the consistency and loyalty the employees show to the company, always a good sign.

Maintenance is another huge reason why my wife and I are so happy here. They respond immediately and remember me by name, even though I don't see them more than once every few months! My pool is always cleaned by a wonderful man named Angel, who also remembers me and does an excellent job.

The area is kept safe by security. The grounds are cleaned very often. Improvements to the community are done on a routine basis (my building was just painted and the doors to the parking garages were all replaced). They even added better lighting to the garage to add a vital bit of security.

<user>108663219877246637049< /user>< Name>
Danielle Faith</Name>
<time>1549118773497</time>< rating>
2< /rating>
< review>
BUYER BEWARE.
OVERPRICED & AWFUL

It seems as if AVA is up to some dirty tricks. If you read through their 358 reviews, you will see that there aren't a whole lot with 4 or less stars. Also, it's the same type of language in each review AND the accounts here only have 1-2 reviews total! I'm only theorizing, but I would bet money that this apartment complex is trying to boost their image with paid reviews.

I lived here for a year in one of their studio apartments. It was an absolute nightmare for $1745 there was no dishwasher and it was built cheaply. If you live on the bottom floor, you're going to hear your upstairs neighbor constantly.

There's a lot of film students here too, so you get a lot of wild and loud poolside parties that management does little to nothing about. Plus, people keep leaving the main building door open or vandalize it so it wont work. There were also multiple car robberies in the carports.

Then management sends out passive aggressive emails about these issues without taking any direct action. However, it was completely worthwhile to harass and accuse me of dumping "personal" trash in mail recycle bins.

I called management and maintenance to let them know that it wasn't me and they ended up giving me a lecture on how I need to understand that doing that causes bugs so they MUST investigate and we were at fault so that's why they reached out. No matter how many times I explained I wasn't the culprit, they refused to apologize and kept insisting I was.

They sent a picture of proof showing that our trash was in the mail. Turns out it was a bunch of old envelopes FROM the mail in a baggie that caused them to freak out.

So, I got basically letured for putting mail trash in the mail area recycling bin!!!

I was renting a studio and managed to find a very nice apartment complex not too far away that was a 1 bedroom for $1695! Can you believe that !? Same and a 1bedroom for less than my studio!?

Just goes to show you what a rip off AVA is.< /review>

<username>Danielle Faith<//username><userid>108663219877246637049</userid>< Text>
BUYER BEWARE.
OVERPRICED & AWFUL

It seems as if AVA is up to some dirty tricks. If you read through their 358 reviews, you will see that there aren't a whole lot with 4 or less stars. Also, it's the same type of language in each review AND the accounts here only have 1-2 reviews total! I'm only theorizing, but I would bet money that this apartment complex is trying to boost their image with paid reviews.

I lived here for a year in one of their studio apartments. It was an absolute nightmare for $1745 there was no dishwasher and it was built cheaply. If you live on the bottom floor, you're going to hear your upstairs neighbor constantly.

There's a lot of film students here too, so you get a lot of wild and loud poolside parties that management does little to nothing about. Plus, people keep leaving the main building door open or vandalize it so it wont work. There were also multiple car robberies in the carports.

Then management sends out passive aggressive emails about these issues without taking any direct action. However, it was completely worthwhile to harass and accuse me of dumping "personal" trash in mail recycle bins.

I called management and maintenance to let them know that it wasn't me and they ended up giving me a lecture on how I need to understand that doing that causes bugs so they MUST investigate and we were at fault so that's why they reached out. No matter how many times I explained I wasn't the culprit, they refused to apologize and kept insisting I was.

They sent a picture of proof showing that our trash was in the mail. Turns out it was a bunch of old envelopes FROM the mail in a baggie that caused them to freak out.

So, I got basically letured for putting mail trash in the mail area recycling bin!!!

I was renting a studio and managed to find a very nice apartment complex not too far away that was a 1 bedroom for $1695! Can you believe that !? Same and a 1bedroom for less than my studio!?

Just goes to show you what a rip off AVA is.</Text>

<Text>I signed a one year lease and ended up staying barely making it a month. You see, while they advertise renovated apartments they really just slap on a new coat of paint every time someone moves out. The walls are paper thin. Let me actually be honest. I moved out because my upstairs neighbors were so loud that living underneath them was impossible. If someone above you has a dog, you'll hear it. If people around you are having guests over, you'll hear it.

Had my boyfriend ask management to do something about it, but of course nothing changed. After barely sleeping for 2 weeks it was time to leave.

I had ants crawling out of my bathtub two days after the move in date even though the bathroom was still clean.

Don't do it. Overpriced for what you get. Looks way nicer than what you actually end up getting.

Sales team is incredibly good at their jobs, though. And try to be helpful. But there's only so much you can do when the apartment itself is faulty and so are your neighbors.</Text><Pictures>None<//Pictures>< resp>

<review>The staff is GREAT, but the buildings and windows are so old there's absolutely no noise insulation. If you are a light sleeper or have a baby, do not even consider moving here. They did superficial updates, so it looks like it's been renovated, but it hasn't where it counts. We've had to submit COUNTLESS work orders for things not working in and around the apartment. The gym seems nice, but it's certainly not membership quality, and machines are constantly broken. Plus, if you've finally had enough and want to get out before your lease is up, they charge 2 months rent to break your lease. We have the worst, most inconsiderate upstairs neighbor right now who constantly wakes our 6 month old throughout the night, and we are stuck here for another 5 months because money is more important than compassion to a big corporation like Avalon. The pool is nice and well-kept and the neighborhood is amazing, but the apartments themselves are too run down and poorly constructed for the premium price tag they charge for them. <Review>Moving is a giant pain in the ass, up there with job searching and online dating. And of course, apartment hunting is best done at a frenzied, panicky pace of a coke fiend. He explained the process to me calmly using small, simple words that could get through my panic mode brain and was very patient with me when I freaked out. I highly recommend working with Nino if you can.

It is great that there are so many team members to assist you on site but sometimes communication gets dropped or emails go unreplied which is common with big teams. <gmapID>0x808f7e1fd1df26a3:0x8726ffb630e8eb44< /gmapID>< Text>
I had one of the best customer service experiences in my life at Pet Food Express, during a particularly difficult period of time. We unfortunately had to surrender our dog, and we came in to see if we could just donate our food and some of the toys that our little pup played with. We weren't even asking for a refund, but just wanted their suggestions on where to donate our stuff! The staff at Pet Food Express was SO NICE! They gave us a full refund on everything (used, unused, it didn't matter), and they didn't even ask for our receipts. They were so supportive, and told us that they understand how difficult this is for people. I can't recommend the store enough - you're really getting the best with them.< /Text>

Everything you would want from a place that helps you do what's best for your pets.
We have and old cat that has decided to be very picky about her food.
Her favorites are no longer her favorites.
Pet Food Express was great about letting us take multiple options home and she what she liked best.
What didn't work, they just asked that we washout the cans, keep our receipts and they refunded us whatever she wouldn't eat... It was in the dozens before we mailed it down.
They returned anything she don't like, no questions. Life savers, really.

<userid>106879714782764310813< /userid><username>Myla</username>< Time>
1465910826379</Time>
< Rate>
5<//Rate>
< Text>
I shop at many PFEs, and I've always had a great experience. The staff is friendly and very knowledgeable about all the products, especially the food. PFE has a large selection of premium pet food including frozen and freeze-dried raw food. They have a buy 3, get 1 free on cat and dog food and cat toys (and possibly other items). This location also has a kitty adoption center, so I always stop by to say hello. I'm a very price conscious buyer, but I don't even bother checking prices elsewhere (I think they price match, but they definitely take just about any coupon) because I like supporting this locally owned store, and I know they donate lots of food to the local shelters. There's an in-house VIP Pet Care Clinic open certain hours and a doggie wash area. And lastly, they have selections for other pets - birds, small mammals like my guinea pig, fish, and herps.<//Text>
